Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.select

Interface SelectService

All Superinterfaces:
Insertion
All Known Implementing Classes:
SelectServiceImpl
public interface SelectService extends Insertion
Provides an interface for interacting with select components in a UI automation framework, enabling selection of multiple options and retrieval of their states or availability. By referencing a SelectComponentType and the DEFAULT_TYPE, implementations can manage different styles of dropdown or multi-select elements with consistent operations.

Classes implementing this interface typically leverage Selenium-based approaches for identifying containers (via SmartWebElement) or using direct locators (via By), ensuring robust and flexible automation across various UI designs.

This interface also extends the Insertion contract, thereby supporting scenarios where select components are part of automated data entry flows.
